                <h1>Understanding Disposition in Criminal Cases</h1>
                <p>In a criminal case, "disposition" refers to the outcome or resolution of legal proceedings. It can include various results such as a conviction, acquittal, plea bargain, or dismissal of charges. Understanding the disposition is crucial for assessing the consequences for the defendant and the implications for future legal matters.</p>
